  "prompt": "Romance (love): Do you still trust your heart after a break up intensive love story?",
  "response": "Here's a thoughtful perspective on trusting your heart after a painful breakup:\n\nHealing after a heartbreak takes time, but trusting your heart again is possible:\n\n1. Emotional Recovery\n- Allow yourself to feel pain\n- Process grief and emotions\n- Learn from the experience\n- Don't rush into a new relationship\n\n2. Self-Reflection\n- Understand what went wrong\n- Recognize personal growth opportunities\n- Heal internal emotional wounds\n- Rebuild self-confidence\n\n3. Heart's Resilience\n- Love is still possible\n- Past pain doesn't define future relationships\n- Each relationship teaches valuable lessons\n- Your heart can heal and love again\n\n4. Rebuilding Trust\n- Be patient with yourself\n- Open yourself gradually\n- Trust your intuition\n- Set healthy boundaries\n\n5. Positive Perspective\n- View heartbreak as a learning experience\n- Believe in love's potential\n- Maintain hope\n- Stay emotionally open\n\n6. Personal Growth\n- Focus on self-improvement\n- Develop emotional intelligence\n- Build stronger self-understanding\n- Create a fulfilling life independently\n\nRemember: Your heart is stronger than past pain. Healing is a journey, and love remains possible.\n\nWould you like to discuss healing after heartbreak more deeply?",
